'''Bruno Miguel Borges Fernandes''' ({{IPA|pt-PT|ˈbɾunu fɨɾˈnɐ̃dɨʃ|lang}};<ref>{{cite web |last=Burns |first=Euan |date=30 September 2021 |title='We ought to try more': how to pronounce footballers' names |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/the-set-pieces-blog/2021/sep/30/how-pronounce-footballers-names-bruno-fernandes-gianluigi-buffon-wojciech-szczesny |access-date=11 May 2023 |website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> born 8 September 1994) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for, and [[Captain (association football)|captain]]s, {{English football updater|ManchesU}} club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. Known for his creative output, vision, goal scoring ability, and passing, he is widely regarded as one of the best midfielders in the world.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Stronge |first=Mark White Contributions from Isaac Stacey |last2=Nee |first2=Chris |last3=Gennery |first3=Ewan |last4=published |first4=Matthew Holt |date=2025-12-12 |title=Ranked! The 20 best attacking midfielders in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/person/player/best-attacking-midfielders-in-the-world |access-date=2026-01-11 |website=FourFourTwo |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-22 |title=The 25 Best Attacking Midfielders in World Soccer—Ranked |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-attacking-midfielders-in-world-soccer-ranked |access-date=2026-01-11 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-04 |title=2025 FC 100: Bellingham among best attacking midfielders in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45178766/2025-fc-100-bellingham-best-attacking-midfielders-mens-soccer |access-date=2026-01-11 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

Fernandes started his career at Italian [[Serie B]] side [[Novara Calcio|Novara]] but soon made a move to [[Serie A]] side [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in 2013, followed by [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] three years later. After five years in Italy, he signed with [[Sporting CP]] in 2017. He won back-to-back [[Taça da Liga|Taças da Liga]] in [[2017–18 Taça da Liga|2018]] and [[2018–19 Taça da Liga|2019]], as well as the [[Taça de Portugal]], leading to him being named in the Primeira Liga Team of the Year and [[LPFP Primeira Liga Player of the Year|Primeira Liga Player of the Year]] in both seasons. In [[2018–19 Sporting CP season|2018–19]], he scored a record of 33 goals in all competitions, making him the highest-scoring Portuguese midfielder and the highest-scoring midfielder in Europe in a single season.

In January 2020, Fernandes signed with United for an initial €55&nbsp;million (£47&nbsp;million), becoming at the time the second-highest fee for a Portuguese player leaving the domestic league. He has become a focal player for United, making more than 300 appearances for the club. Collectively, he has won the [[FA Cup]] and [[EFL Cup]]; he also contributed to the club reaching the [[UEFA Europa League]] final in 2021 and 2025, being the competition's [[UEFA Europa League top scorers|top scorer]] in those two seasons, and the FA Cup final in 2023. In [[2025–26 Premier League|2026]], Fernandes was awarded both the [[FWA Footballer of the Year]] and [[Premier League Player of the Season]]. He was also won the [[Premier League Playmaker of the Season]] for registering 21 assists, simultaneously breaking the record for [[Premier League records and statistics#Assists|most assists in a single Premier League season]].

Fernandes is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[Portugal national under-20 football team|under-20]], [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21]] and [[Portugal national under-23 football team|under-23]] levels. He represented Portugal at the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2016 Summer Olympics]]. He made his senior international debut in 2017, being chosen in Portugal's squads for the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]], the [[UEFA European Championship]] in [[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024]], and the [[UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League Finals]] in [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019]] and [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|2025]], winning the latter competition both times while also being named to its [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals#Awards|Team of the Tournament]] on home soil in 2019.

==Early life==
Fernandes was born in [[Maia, Portugal|Maia]], [[Metropolitan Area of Porto]]. Growing up, he supported [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Davies |first=Matt |date=1 October 2020 |title=Bruno Fernandes reveals tears of joy in emotional tale of Man Utd move |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-united-fc-transfer-news-bruno-fernandes-tears-of-joy-childhood-a4561041.html |access-date=26 July 2023 |website=Evening Standard }}</ref> During his childhood, Fernandes used to play football on the streets with his older brother Ricardo, who was also a professional football player.<ref name=Bruno8>{{cite video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8rgk-YGraUc&t=16s&ab_channel=SoccerStories-OhMyGoal |title=8 things you didn't know about Bruno Fernandes |author=Oh My Goal |via=YouTube |access-date=12 December 2020}}</ref> His father, who had emigrated to Switzerland, wanted Fernandes to move with him, but he refused, due to the standard of [[Football in Switzerland|Swiss football]] at the time.<ref name=BrunoEarly>{{cite video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WJ8N6xAUgJY&t=117s&ab_channel=Goal90 |title=10 Things you didn't know about Bruno Fernandes |author=Goal 90 |via=YouTube |access-date=24 August 2021}}</ref><ref name=Bruno99>{{cite video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PmMDiJOXQsM&t=88s&ab_channel=SoccerStories-OhMyGoal |title=99 facts that make Bruno Fernandes so special |author=Oh My Goal |via=YouTube |access-date=1 June 2021}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Early career===
Fernandes began his youth career at local club [[F.C. Infesta|Infesta]]. Growing up, Fernandes was offered a youth contract at [[FC Porto|Porto]]'s academy, but he went to local rivals Boavista, who offered him transportation to training, with his parents being unable to take him to [[Porto]] on a daily basis.<ref name=BrunoEarly/> Fernandes played most of his youth football with Boavista, starting his career as a [[centre-back]], before being converted to an [[attacking midfielder]] at the age of 15, following a loan to Pasteleira.<ref name=BrunoEarly/><ref name=Bruno99/>

===Spell in Italy===
==== Novara (2012–2013)====
On 27 August 2012, he joined [[Novara Calcio|Novara]] in Italy.<ref>{{cite news|last=Roseiro|first=Bruno|date=27 June 2017|title=Bruno Fernandes. O miúdo que começou a rolar na capital do hóquei|language=pt|trans-title=Bruno Fernandes. The kid who started rolling in the hockey capital|newspaper=Observador|location=Lisbon|url=https://observador.pt/2017/06/27/bruno-fernandes-o-miudo-que-comecou-a-rolar-na-capital-do-hoquei/|url-status=live|access-date=25 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128051013/https://observador.pt/2017/06/27/bruno-fernandes-o-miudo-que-comecou-a-rolar-na-capital-do-hoquei/|archive-date=28 November 2020}}</ref> Fernandes initially struggled in his new life in Italy, after suffering from homesickness and also had problems learning Italian. After his girlfriend moved to Italy, Fernandes quickly learned the language and began settling in the country, being nicknamed the "[[Diego Maradona|Maradona]] of Novara" and the "Mini [[Rui Costa]]".<ref name=Bruno99/> After only a few weeks with the youth sides, Fernandes was promoted to the first team in [[Serie B]], and went on to appear in slightly more than half of the league games during the [[2012–13 Serie B|2012–13 season]], helping his team to fifth place and the promotion play-offs.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Italian Serie B Table|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/table/_/season/2012/league/ITA.2|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201231125950/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/table/_/season/2012/league/ITA.2|archive-date=31 December 2020|access-date=2 December 2020|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref>

==== Udinese and Sampdoria (2013–2017)====
In summer 2013, [[Serie A]] clubs [[Inter Milan]] and [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] wanted to sign him, but instead, Fernandes decided to sign for [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in a [[Co-ownership (association football)|co-ownership deal]], which promised him first-team opportunities.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://it.sports.yahoo.com/blog/euroscout-it/bruno-fernandes-l-ennesimo-colpo-dell-udinese-095838834--sow.html |title=Bruno Fernandes, l'ennesimo colpo dell'Udinese |trans-title=Bruno Fernandes, Udinese's umpteenth steal |website=Yahoo! Sports |language=it |date=3 December 2013 |access-date=27 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408021728/https://it.sports.yahoo.com/blog/euroscout-it/bruno-fernandes-l-ennesimo-colpo-dell-udinese-095838834--sow.html |archive-date=8 April 2016}}</ref> He made his debut in Serie A on 3 November, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 0–3 home loss against Inter Milan.<ref>{{cite web |date=3 November 2013 |title=Udinese-Inter 0–3: Palacio, raddoppia Rannocchia, tris di Alvarez |trans-title=Udinese-Inter 0–3: Palacio, Rannocchia doubles it, Alvarez gets third |url=http://www.calciomercato.com/inter/udinese-inter-diretta-989532 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927034817/https://www.calciomercato.com/news/udinese-inter-diretta-989532 |archive-date=27 September 2020 |access-date=27 March 2016 |website=Calciomercato.com |publisher=Calcioinfinito |language=it}}</ref> Fernandes scored his first league goal on 7 December, in a 3–3 draw at [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web |date=7 December 2013 |title=Pareggio al San Paolo, doppietta di Pandev e gol di Dzemaili per gli azzurri |trans-title=Draw at San Paolo, Pandev brace and Dzemaili goal for the blues |url=http://www.sscnapoli.it/static/news/Napoli-Udinese-3-3-1462.aspx |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927034821/https://www.sscnapoli.it/static/news/Napoli-Udinese-3-3-1462.aspx |archive-date=27 September 2020 |access-date=27 March 2016 |publisher=[[S.S.C. Napoli]] |language=it}}</ref> He scored again in the second match between the sides, a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/19-04-2014/udinese-napoli-1-1-gol-callejon-bruno-fernandes-espulso-fernandez-80482800612.shtml |title=Udinese-Napoli 1–1, gol di Callejon e Bruno Fernandes. Espulso Fernandez |trans-title=Udinese-Napoli 1–1, goals from Callejon and Bruno Fernandes. Fernandez sent off |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |location=Milan |first=Mimmo |last=Malfitano |language=it |date=19 April 2014 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref>

On 16 August 2016, Fernandes moved to [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] on loan with an obligation to be signed permanently.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.football-italia.net/89837/official-sampdoria-sign-bruno-fernandes |title=Official: Sampdoria sign Bruno Fernandes |website=Football Italia |publisher=Tiro Media |date=16 August 2016 |access-date=26 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/calcio-mercato/2016/08/16-14450411/ufficiale_bruno_fernandes_alla_sampdoria/ |title=Ufficiale: Bruno Fernandes alla Sampdoria|trans-title=Official: Bruno Fernandes to Sampdoria |newspaper=Corriere dello Sport |location=Rome |language=it |date=16 August 2016 |access-date=26 August 2016}}</ref> He made his league debut twelve days later, playing six minutes in a 2–1 home win over [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ecodibergamo.it/stories/Sport/sampdoria-atalanta-le-ultime-notizieil-modulo-e-il-3-5-2-gioca-carmona_1198963_11/ |title=Atalanta ancora ko: 2–1 per la Samp – Non riesce la rimonta in dieci uomini|trans-title=Atalanta down again: 2–1 to Samp – No comeback with ten men |newspaper=L'Eco di Bergamo |language=it |date=28 August 2016 |access-date=28 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180520124145/https://www.ecodibergamo.it/stories/Sport/sampdoria-atalanta-le-ultime-notizieil-modulo-e-il-3-5-2-gioca-carmona_1198963_11/ |archive-date=20 May 2018}}</ref> Fernandes scored his first goal for his new team on 26 September, in a 1–2 away loss to [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/2016/09/26-15799051/serie_a_cagliari-sampdoria_2-1_joao_pedro_e_melchiorri_show_bruno_fernandes_non_basta/ |title=Serie A, Cagliari-Sampdoria 2–1: Joao Pedro e Melchiorri show, ma che papera di Viviano|trans-title=Serie A, Cagliari-Sampdoria 2–1: Joao Pedro and Melchiorri show, but what a blunder by Viviano |newspaper=Corriere dello Sport |location=Rome |language=it |date=26 September 2016 |access-date=28 June 2017}}</ref> He scored five goals in 33 Serie A appearances during [[2016–17 Serie A|the campaign]],<ref name=Soccerway/> helping them to finish in tenth position.<ref>{{Cite web|title=League Table {{!}} Lega Serie A|url=http://www.legaseriea.it/en/serie-a/league-table|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109011819/http://www.legaseriea.it/en/serie-a/league-table|archive-date=9 November 2020|access-date=2 December 2020|website=legaseriea.it|publisher=[[Serie A]]}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
====2017–2018: Primeira Liga Player of the Year====
On 27 June 2017, after returning from the [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], Fernandes joined [[Sporting CP]] on a five-year deal, for a reported fee of €8.5&nbsp;million plus bonuses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/liga/27-06-2017/oficial-sampdoria-confirma-bruno-fernandes-no-sporting?_ga=2.128693580.1153459493.1498137173-1125892984.1471973876 |title=Sporting: Bruno Fernandes com cláusula de 100 milhões|trans-title=Sporting: Bruno Fernandes with 100 million clause |website=Maisfutebol |publisher=IOL |language=pt |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref> On 6 August, Fernandes made his debut for the club in a 2–0 home victory against [[C.D. Aves|Desportivo das Aves]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://tribunaexpresso.pt/sporting/2017-08-06-Olha-o-primeiro-11-da-epoca-do-Sporting---com-Adrien-e-com-espaco-para-Bruno-Fernandes |title=Look at the first 11 of the Sporting season – with Adrien and with space for Bruno Fernandes |access-date=20 March 2021 |website=Tribuna Expresso |language=pt}}</ref> He scored four goals in his first five [[Primeira Liga]] games, including a brace in a 5–0 away win against [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/jorge-jesus-dupla-bruno-fernandes-bas-dost-nao-serve-para-todos-os-jogos.html |title=Jorge Jesus: "Dupla Bruno Fernandes-Bas Dost não serve para todos os jogos" |trans-title=Jorge Jesus: «Bruno Fernandes-Bas Dost duo is not good for every game» |newspaper=Record |location=Lisbon |language=pt |date=19 August 2017 |access-date=27 June 2017 |archive-date=27 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927034914/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/jorge-jesus-dupla-bruno-fernandes-bas-dost-nao-serve-para-todos-os-jogos/ |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/interior/bruno-fernandes-arranca-como-balakov-8760054.html |title=Bruno Fernandes arranca como Balakov |trans-title=Bruno Fernandes gets going like Balakov |newspaper=O Jogo |location=Porto |first1=Duarte |last1=Tornesi |first2=Rafael |last2=Toucedo |language=pt |date=10 September 2017 |access-date=12 September 2017 |archive-date=27 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927034922/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/bruno-fernandes-arranca-como-balakov-8760054.html/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernandes' first appearance in the [[UEFA Champions League]] group stage was on 12 September, where he put the visitors 3–0 ahead in the 43rd minute of an eventual [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League|3–2 win]] at [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pt.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2021594--olympiacos-vs-sporting-cp/ |title=Sporting derrota Olympiacos na Grécia |trans-title=Sporting defeat Olympiacos in Greece |publisher=UEFA |language=pt |date=12 September 2017 |access-date=13 September 2017 |archive-date=15 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915173910/http://pt.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2018/matches/round=2000881/match=2021594/postmatch/report/index.html?rss=2500275+Sporting+derrota+Olympiacos+na+Gr%C3%A9cia |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished his first season with 16 goals across all competitions, second only to [[Bas Dost]] and provided 20 assists, being named in the [[2017–18 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Primeira Liga Team of the Year]] and [[LPFP Primeira Liga Player of the Year|Primeira Liga Player of the Year]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/quarta-vez-de-bruno-fernandes.html |title=Quarta vez de Bruno Fernandes |trans-title=Fourth time for Bruno Fernandes |newspaper=Record |location=Lisbon |language=pt |date=29 April 2018 |access-date=25 May 2018 |archive-date=27 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927034929/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/quarta-vez-de-bruno-fernandes/ |url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 15 May 2018, Fernandes and several of his teammates, including coaches, were injured following an attack by around 50 Sporting supporters at the club's training ground after the team finished third in the league and missed out on Champions League qualification.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/pt-pt/desporto/sporting/19-jogadores-do-sporting-contam-tudo-sobre-o-ataque-a-alcochete-e-como-palhinha-protegeu-montero/ar-AAxF6FQ |title=19 jogadores do Sporting contam tudo sobre o ataque a Alcochete (e como Palhinha protegeu Montero)|trans-title=19 Sporting players tell everything about the attack at Alcochete (and how Palinha protected Montero) |publisher=MSN |language=pt |date=23 May 2018 |access-date=24 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportsjoe.ie/football/sporting-lisbon-attack-160186 |title=Sporting Lisbon players attacked at training ground after failing to secure Champions League spot |website=SportsJOE.ie |publisher=Maximum Media |first=Ben |last=Kiley |date=15 May 2018 |access-date=16 May 2018}}</ref> Despite the events, the team agreed to play in [[2018 Taça de Portugal Final|the final]] of the [[Taça de Portugal]] scheduled for the following weekend,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44142885 |title=Sporting Lisbon: Players agree to play Portuguese Cup final after attack |website=BBC Sport |date=16 May 2018 |access-date=2 June 2018}}</ref> eventually losing to Desportivo das Aves.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/taca-portugal/noticias/interior/aves-ganha-a-taca-de-portugal-gracas-a-bis-de-guedes-9360212.html |title=Aves ganha a Taça de Portugal graças a bis de Guedes |trans-title=Aves win Portuguese Cup thanks to Guedes brace |newspaper=O Jogo |location=Porto |language=pt |date=20 May 2018 |access-date=26 July 2018 |archive-date=17 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221017203439/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/taca-portugal/noticias/interior/aves-ganha-a-taca-de-portugal-gracas-a-bis-de-guedes-9360212.html |url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernandes was named the Primeira Liga Player of the Year on 6 July.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/interior/bruno-fernandes-eleito-melhor-jogador-da-i-liga-em-201718-9561926.html |title=Bruno Fernandes eleito melhor jogador da 1 Liga |trans-title=Bruno Fernandes voted best player of the 1 League |newspaper=O Jogo |location=Porto |language=pt |date=6 July 2018 |access-date=18 August 2018 |archive-date=27 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927034954/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/bruno-fernandes-eleito-melhor-jogador-da-i-liga-em-201718-9561926.html/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> Four days later he signed a new five-year contract with a €100&nbsp;million release clause,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/sporting-lisbon/transfer-talk/news/bruno-fernandes-pens-sporting-lisbon-deal_330281.html |title=Bruno Fernandes pens Sporting Lisbon deal |publisher=Sports Mole |date=10 July 2018 |access-date=18 August 2018}}</ref> having turned back on his original decision to leave the [[Estádio José Alvalade]] following the departure of club president [[Bruno de Carvalho]], and being given an improved salary in the process.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abola.pt/nacional/Noticias/Ver/739382 |title=Bruno Fernandes passará a ganhar o dobro |trans-title=Bruno Fernandes will earn twice as much |newspaper=A Bola |location=Lisbon |language=pt |date=8 July 2018 |access-date=9 July 2018 |archive-date=10 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710011249/https://www.abola.pt/nacional/Noticias/Ver/739382 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

====2018–2020: Highest-scoring midfielder in Europe====
Fernandes scored his 23rd competitive goal of the [[2018–19 Sporting CP season|2018–19 campaign]] during a 3–1 home win against [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]] on 3 March 2019, through a late [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]], surpassing [[António Luís Alves Ribeiro Oliveira|António Oliveira]]'s club record for goals by a midfielder in a season, set in [[1981–82 Primeira Divisão|1981–82]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://observador.pt/2019/03/03/bruno-fernandes-e-um-recorde-que-fica-bem-na-fotografia-medio-bate-registo-de-golos-de-oliveira/ |title=Bruno Fernandes e um recorde que fica bem na fotografia: médio bate registo de golos de Oliveira|trans-title=Bruno Fernandes and a record that looks pretty good: midfielder breaks Oliveira's scoring figures |newspaper=Observador |location=Lisbon |first=Bruno |last=Roseiro |language=pt |date=3 March 2019 |access-date=5 March 2019}}</ref> On 5 May, he scored a [[hat-trick]] in an 8–1 away rout of [[Belenenses SAD]], in the process becoming the highest-scoring Portuguese midfielder in a single season of all time, with 31 goals to his name.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1143-sporting-put-eight-past-belenenses-following-big-wins-for-title-bound-benfica-and-fc-porto |title=Sporting put eight past Belenenses following big wins for title-tussling Benfica and FC Porto |website=PortuGOAL.net |first=Patrick |last=Ribeiro |date=5 May 2019 |access-date=7 May 2019}}</ref> He scored his 33rd and final goal of the season on 25 May 2019, during Sporting's victory against Porto in the Taça de Portugal final.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1166-sporting-complete-cup-double-over-porto-to-secure-taca-de-portugal-title |title=Sporting complete cup-double over Porto and secure Taça de Portugal title |website=PortuGOAL.net |first=Patrick |last=Ribeiro |date=25 May 2019 |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=fdj/> He was named Primeira Liga Player of the Year for the second successive year for his performances in the 2018–19 season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/sporting/06-07-2019/bruno-fernandes-eleito-o-melhor-jogador-da-liga-em-18-19 |title=Bruno Fernandes eleito o melhor jogador da Liga em 18/19 |trans-title=Bruno Fernandes elected the best player of the League in 18/19 |website=maisfutebol.iol.pt |language=pt |date=5 July 2019 |access-date=18 May 2020}}</ref>

He scored seven goals in his first 10 appearances of the [[2019–20 Sporting CP season|2019–20 season]], including a run of scoring in six consecutive appearances.{{citation needed|date=March 2025}} This made him the third Sporting player in the 21st century to score in six or more consecutive appearances for the club, after [[Mário Jardel]] and Bas Dost.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.zerozero.pt/news.php?id=264683 |title=Ainda há palavras para os registos históricos deste senhor capitão? |trans-title=Are there still words for this captain's historical record? |website=zerozero.pt |language=pt |date=4 October 2019 |access-date=17 May 2020}}</ref> On 28 November, he scored twice and assisted the other two goals in a 4–0 victory over [[PSV Eindhoven]], which guaranteed Sporting qualification to the knockout stages of the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1395-europa-league-all-smiles-for-sporting-porto-and-braga-vitoria-unlucky-again |title=Europa League: All smiles for Sporting, Porto and Braga, Vitória unlucky again |website=PortuGOAL.net |date=29 November 2019 |access-date=17 May 2020}}</ref>

===Manchester United===
====2019–2020: Europa League top scorer====
On 29 January 2020, English club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] confirmed they had reached an agreement with Sporting to sign Fernandes for a fee reportedly worth up to €80&nbsp;million (£67.6&nbsp;million),<ref>{{cite news |title=Bruno Fernandes: Manchester United agree deal with Sporting Lisbon |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51301424 |website=BBC Sport |date=29 January 2020 |access-date=2 February 2020}}</ref> subject to him passing a medical and agreeing personal terms.<ref>{{cite web |title=United agree deal to sign Bruno Fernandes |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/manchester-united-agree-deal-to-sign-bruno-fernandes |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=29 January 2020 |access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref> The transfer was officially completed the following day, for an initial fee of around €55&nbsp;million (£47&nbsp;million),<ref>{{cite news |title=Bruno Fernandes: Manchester United sign Sporting Lisbon midfielder |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51292312 |website=BBC Sport |date=30 January 2020 |access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> plus up to €25&nbsp;million (£21&nbsp;million) in add-ons and 10% of the profits of a future sale.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sporting oficializa venda de Bruno Fernandes ao Man. United: todos os detalhes do negócio |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/sporting-oficializa-venda-de-bruno-fernandes-ao-manchester-united-os-detalhes-do-negocio |newspaper=Record |location=Lisbon |language=pt-PT |date=29 January 2020 |access-date=2 February 2020 |archive-date=2 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202221656/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/sporting-oficializa-venda-de-bruno-fernandes-ao-manchester-united-os-detalhes-do-negocio |url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernandes signed a five-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=Man Utd complete the signing of Bruno Fernandes from Sporting |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-complete-the-signing-of-bruno-fernandes-from-sporting |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=30 January 2020 |access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> 

He made his debut on 1 February, playing the full 90 minutes of a goalless home draw to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Manchester United 0–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51246502 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 February 2020 |access-date=2 February 2020}}</ref> In United's 2–0 away win over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on 17 February, he provided an assist for the second goal, a header from [[Harry Maguire]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Chelsea 0–2 Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51439302 |website=BBC Sport |date=17 February 2020 |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref> Fernandes came on as a late substitute against [[Club Brugge]] in a 1–1 draw on his European debut for the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Club Bruges 1–1 Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51533294 |website=BBC Sport |date=20 February 2020 |access-date=20 February 2020}}</ref> He scored his first United goal against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on 23 February, converting from the penalty spot in a 3–0 victory at [[Old Trafford]], a match in which he also provided an assist for the third goal scored by [[Mason Greenwood]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester United 3–0 Watford |url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/46871 |publisher=Premier League |date=23 February 2020 |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> His first European goal for the club came in the second leg of their UEFA Europa League round of 32 tie against Club Brugge at Old Trafford, in which he scored a penalty, helping them to a 5–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web |first=Emlyn |last=Begley |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51623256 |title=Manchester United 5–0 Club Brugge |website=BBC Sport |date=27 February 2020 |access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> On 16 March, Fernandes was voted as the [[Premier League Player of the Month]] for February.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/1644143 |title=Fernandes: I'm happy with my start at Man Utd |publisher=Premier League |date=16 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>

On 30 June, Fernandes scored his first brace for the club in a 3–0 win over [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Shamoon |last=Hafez |title=Brighton 0–3 Man Utd: Visitors score through Greenwood and Fernandes' double |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52072990 |website=BBC Sport |date=30 June 2020 |access-date=30 June 2020}}</ref> For his performances in June, he won multiple club and Premier League awards, including Premier League Player of the Month and Goal of the Month, becoming the first player to win both awards concurrently in Premier League history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/1715420 |title=Fernandes wins EA SPORTS Player of the Month again |publisher=Premier League |date=10 July 2020 |access-date=10 July 2020}}</ref><ref name="GOTMJun20" /> He also became the first Manchester United player to win back to back Premier League Player of the Month awards since [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] in the [[2006–07 FA Premier League|2006–07 season]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Sam |last=France |title=Fernandes matches Ronaldo's Man Utd feat with latest Premier League Player of the Month award |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/fernandes-matches-ronaldo-man-utd-premier-league-player-of/19bgfcebthnuq1u96efo56gyh2 |work=Goal (website) |date=10 July 2020 |access-date=13 July 2020}}</ref> In September, Fernandes was named as the winner of Manchester United's [[Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year]] award, given to the club's best player from the previous season.<ref name="MUNPOTY20">{{cite news |first=Joe |last=Ganley |title=Fernandes voted Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-wins-sir-matt-busby-player-of-the-year-award-for-2019-20 |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=18 September 2020 |access-date=18 September 2020}}</ref>

====2020–2021: Individual success and Europa League final====
On 26 September, Fernandes scored his first goal of the season against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in the 100th minute of a 3–2 win at the [[Amex Stadium]]; it was one of the latest goals in Premier League history, and came after referee [[Chris Kavanagh (referee)|Chris Kavanagh]] had blown the final whistle, before a [[video assistant referee]] awarded United a penalty which Fernandes converted.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wright |first=Chris |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/manchester-united/story/4192046/how-did-man-uniteds-bruno-fernandes-score-winner-vs-brighton-after-full-time-whistle-was-blown |title=How did Man United's Bruno Fernandes score winner vs. Brighton AFTER full-time whistle was blown? |date=26 September 2020 |access-date=15 January 2021 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> On 7 November, Fernandes scored a brace and provided an assist against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] to secure a 3–1 away win.<ref>{{cite news |last=Magowan |first=Alistair |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54758065 |title=Everton 1–3 Manchester United: Bruno Fernandes scores twice at Goodison |date=7 November 2020 |access-date=8 November 2020 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He was named Premier League Player of the Month for November in recognition of his four goals and one assist that month,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/1931610 |title=Fernandes voted November EA SPORTS Player of the Month |publisher=Premier League |date=11 December 2020 |access-date=11 December 2020}}</ref> and again in December after scoring three goals and providing four assists in that month, becoming the first player to win the award four times in a single calendar year.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hall |first=Peter |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/manchester-united/bruno-fernandes-player-of-the-month-b1787879.html |title=Manchester United's Bruno Fernandes sets Premier League Player of the Month record |date=15 January 2021 |access-date=15 January 2021 |work=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12188313/fernandes-named-player-of-the-month-smith-wins-manager-award |title=Bruno Fernandes: Manchester United midfielder named Premier League Player of the Month for December |date=15 January 2021 |access-date=15 January 2021 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> He scored one goal and made two assists in United's Premier League record-equalling [[Manchester United F.C. 9–0 Southampton F.C.|9–0]] home win against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] on 2 February 2021.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Stone|first=Simon|date=2 February 2021|title=Man Utd beat nine-man Southampton 9–0 |website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55806211 |access-date=3 February 2021}}</ref> He finished third in terms of top goalscorers in the league with 18 goals and second among the top assist providers with 12.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://footballexpress.co.uk/premier-league-top-5-midfielders/|title=Premier League: Top 5 midfielders|website=Football Express.co.uk|access-date=2 June 2021|archive-date=5 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210605093559/https://footballexpress.co.uk/premier-league-top-5-midfielders/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In April, a day after United had announced their plan to join the [[European Super League]] along with 11 other clubs, Fernandes became the first potential European Super League player to comment on this, stating his disapproval: "Dreams can't be [bought]."<ref>{{cite news |title='Dreams can't be bought': Bruno Fernandes breaks silence on Super League |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/football/super-league-fernandes-ozil-herrera-lovren-reactions-7280517/ |access-date=26 July 2021 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |date=20 April 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bruno Fernandes and Joao Cancelo oppose European Super League: Dreams can't be bought |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2021/04/19/607db7ff46163fbd388b4574.html |access-date=26 July 2021 |work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |date=19 April 2021}}</ref> By the next day, United withdrew from the prospective league, which was also announced to be "suspended" that day, amid a backlash from players, managers, football institutions, politicians, fans and the media.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Luckhurst |first1=Samuel |title=Manchester United withdraw from Super League |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-united-super-league-glazer-20430997 |access-date=26 July 2021 |work=[[Manchester Evening News]] |date=20 April 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Marcotti |first=Gabriele |title=Super League suspended: Why English clubs pulled out, and what's next for them and UEFA |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-marcottis-musings/story/4365465/super-league-suspended-why-english-clubs-pulled-outwhats-next-for-them-and-uefa |access-date=26 July 2021 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=21 April 2021}}</ref> On 29 April, he scored twice and assisted two more goals in a 6–2 home win over [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in the first leg of the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] semi-finals;<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Manchester United 6–2 Roma: United win eight-goal thriller in Europa League semi-final |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56892065 |website=BBC Sport |date=29 April 2021 |access-date=29 April 2021}}</ref> and provided an assist in a 3–2 defeat in the return leg, which allowed United to advance to the final 8–5 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Roma 3–2 Man Utd (5–8 on aggregate): Solskjaer's side through to Europa League final |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56973031 |website=BBC Sport |date=6 May 2021 |access-date=6 May 2021}}</ref> On 18 May, he was named as the winner of the Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year award for the second successive season.<ref name="MUNPOTY21">{{cite web |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-is-2020-21-sir-matt-busby-player-of-the-year |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year Revealed |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=18 May 2021 |access-date=18 May 2021}}</ref> On 26 May, United drew 1–1 against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] after extra-time, in the [[2021 UEFA Europa League Final|Europa League Final]], but eventually lost on penalties, despite Fernandes netting his spot kick in the shoot-out.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0269-125f1aaaeb0d-c59e8a06ac14-1000--villarreal-1-1-manchester-united-aet-11-10-pens-spanish-side/ |title=Villarreal 1–1 Manchester United (aet, 11–10 pens): Spanish side win Europa League in marathon shoot-out |publisher=UEFA |date=26 May 2021}}</ref>

====2021–2022: Champions League top assist provider====
[[File:Manchester United v Leeds United, 14 August 2021 (14).jpg|thumb|upright|Fernandes appearing for Manchester United in a [[Premier League]] match against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] during the [[2021–22 Manchester United F.C. season|2021–22 season]]]]
On 14 August, in the opening match of the [[2021–22 Premier League|Premier League season]], Fernandes scored a hat-trick against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] in a 5–1 win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/14/manchester-united-leeds-premier-league-match-report|title=Bruno Fernandes hits hat-trick as Manchester United crush Leeds |website=The Guardian |date=14 August 2021}}</ref> He then scored in the team's next home game against Newcastle United,<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Cristiano Ronaldo twice scores as Manchester United beat Newcastle |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58437003 |website=BBC Sport |date=11 September 2021 |access-date=11 September 2021}}</ref> before missing a last minute penalty against Aston Villa two weeks later that would have salvaged a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite news |first=Neil |last=Johnston |title=Manchester United 0–1 Aston Villa |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58606473 |website=BBC Sport |date=25 September 2021 |access-date=27 September 2021}}</ref> He later posted an apology for his penalty miss on [[Instagram]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12418426/bruno-fernandes-manchester-united-midfielder-vows-to-come-back-stronger-after-penalty-miss|title=Bruno Fernandes: Manchester United midfielder vows to 'come back stronger' after penalty miss vs Aston Villa|publisher=Sky Sports|date=26 September 2021|access-date=27 September 2021}}</ref> On 23 November, Fernandes provided an assist for [[Jadon Sancho]] in United's 2–0 victory away against Villarreal in the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League group stage|Champions League]], to ensure his team qualification to the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of 16]], becoming the first player to provide an assist in five consecutive matches of a Champions League campaign for an English club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.101greatgoals.com/news/revealed-the-record-bruno-fernandes-set-during-manchester-uniteds-win-over-villarreal/|title=Bruno Fernandes Assist record|website=101GreatGoals|date=23 November 2021|access-date=23 November 2021|archive-date=26 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211126232618/https://www.101greatgoals.com/news/revealed-the-record-bruno-fernandes-set-during-manchester-uniteds-win-over-villarreal/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 2 December, Fernandes made his 100th appearance for the club, opening the scoring in United's 3–2 home win over [[Arsenal F.C.–Manchester United F.C. rivalry|rivals]] [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] at Old Trafford.<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Man Utd 3–2 Arsenal: Cristiano Ronaldo passes 800 goals in win tinged with controversy |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59411776 |website=BBC Sport |date=2 December 2021 |access-date=2 December 2021}}</ref>

On 1 April 2022, Fernandes signed a new contract which would keep him at United until June 2026, with the option of a further year.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 April 2022 |title=Bruno Fernandes signs new contract with Man Utd {{!}} Manchester United |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-signs-new-contract-with-man-utd-april-2022 |access-date=1 April 2022}}</ref> On 2 May, he scored his 50th goal for United in the club's 3–0 home win over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Man Utd 3–0 Brentford: Fernandes, Ronaldo & Varane score in morale-boosting win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61212449 |website=BBC Sport |date=2 May 2022|access-date=2 May 2022}}</ref> His performances declined during the season, with Fernandes alongside his teammates struggling and under-performing and with United supporters becoming increasingly frustrated by Fernandes' complaints to referees during matches, and with the club finishing a disappointing sixth place, qualifying for the UEFA Europa League, despite Fernandes being the top assist provider in the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League]], with seven assists in total.<ref>{{cite news |first=James |last=Findlater |title=Frenkie de Jong offers solution to Bruno Fernandes issue that infuriates Manchester United fans|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/de-jong-fernandes-manchester-united-24205305|website=BBC Sport |date=12 June 2022|access-date=5 July 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=23 May 2022 |title=Comparing Messi's PSG record with Ronaldo's at Man Utd in 2021–22 |url=https://www.planetfootball.com/quick-reads/comparing-lionel-messi-psg-record-with-cristiano-ronaldo-at-man-utd-in-2021-22/ |access-date=12 June 2022 |website=Planet Football}}</ref>

====2022–2023: Ending the trophy drought====
On 1 July 2022, United announced that they had changed Fernandes' squad number from 18 to his preferred number 8, the same number he wore during his time for Sporting CP and as a tribute to his birth date and his father, upon the departure of [[Juan Mata]].<ref name=":3">{{cite news |title=Fernandes changes shirt number |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-changes-shirt-number-ahead-of-new-season|date=7 July 2022|access-date=7 July 2022|publisher=Manchester United F.C. |first=Adam |last=Marshall}}</ref> Fernandes scored his first goal of the season on 27 August in a 1–0 away win against Southampton.<ref>{{cite news |title=Southampton 0–1 Man Utd: Bruno Fernandes scores only goal at St Mary's to end dismal away run |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62614445 |work=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2022 |access-date=28 August 2022}}</ref>

On 3 January 2023, Fernandes made his 150th appearance for the club, assisting [[Marcus Rashford]]'s goal in United's 3–0 home win over [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Win a signed Bruno Fernandes shirt |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/win-a-signed-bruno-fernandes-shirt-to-celebrate-his-150th-man-utd-appearance |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=4 January 2023 |access-date=14 January 2023}}</ref> Two weeks later, he was instrumental in United's 2–1 comeback win over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the [[Manchester derby]], scoring a goal that was part of the build-up play for United's controversial equaliser despite Rashford being in an offside position, helping United to extend their winning run to nine in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Man Utd 2–1 Man City: Marcus Rashford scores winner in Manchester derby |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64195236 |access-date=14 January 2023 |work=BBC Sport |date=14 January 2023}}</ref> On 18 January, Fernandes scored in a 1–1 away draw to [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], registering his 100th goal contribution for the club. He also became the United midfielder with the second most goal contributions in the Premier League, only behind [[Paul Scholes]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title='Finally arrived!' – Manchester United fans agree after Bruno Fernandes goal vs Crystal Palace |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-fernandes-goal-palace-26013850 |access-date=18 January 2023 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=18 January 2023}}</ref> On 26 February, Fernandes started in the [[2023 EFL Cup final]] as United beat [[Newcastle United]] 2–0 at [[Wembley Stadium]], winning his first trophy with the club.<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Manchester United 2–0 Newcastle United: Erik Ten Hag's side wins the Carabao Cup for first trophy since 2017 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64693810 |access-date=28 February 2023 |work=BBC Sport |date=26 February 2023}}</ref>

Fernandes created the most chances (119) in the [[2022–23 Premier League]], the highest on record since 2003–04 by a United player in a single campaign. United qualified for the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League]] after securing a third-place finish in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://theanalyst.com/eu/2023/07/introducing-opta-player-ratings-premier-league-star-players-in-2022-23/|title=Introducing Opta Player Ratings: Premier League Star Players in 2022–23|date=27 July 2023|access-date=29 May 2024|author=Opta Analyst|website=theanalyst.com}}</ref> In the [[2023 FA Cup final]], Fernandes equalised for United through a penalty in an eventual 2–1 defeat to local rivals Manchester City.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2023/06/03/manchester-city-united-fa-cup-final-live-score-updates/ |title=Man City one win from Treble after exquisite Gundogan double downs Man Utd |first1=Sam |last1=Wallace |first2=Daniel |last2=Zeqiri |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=3 June 2023 |access-date=4 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jun/03/manchester-city-manchester-united-fa-cup-final-match-report |title=Manchester City hold off Manchester United to win FA Cup and strike Double |first=David |last=Hytner |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=3 June 2023 |access-date=4 June 2023}}</ref>

====2023–present: Club captaincy, FA Cup win, and assist record====
On 20 July 2023, Fernandes was named as Harry Maguire's replacement as [[club captain]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Fernandes named United's new club captain |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/official-statement-man-utd-confirm-bruno-fernandes-as-new-club-captain.|publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=20 July 2023 |access-date=20 July 2023}}</ref> On 26 August, Fernandes scored his first goal of the season, netting a penalty, and also assisting [[Casemiro]] in a 3–2 comeback win over [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester United storm back to beat 10-man Forest with Fernandes spot-on|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/26/manchester-united-nottingham-forest-premier-league-match-report |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=26 August 2023 |access-date=8 September 2023}}</ref> The following months, United endured a difficult start to the season, most notably in the [[2023–24 Premier League|Premier League]] and [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League#Group Stage|Champions League]], finishing last in their group.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bate |first=Adam |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/manchester-united-vs-bayern-munich/498964 |title=Man Utd 0–1 Bayern Munich: Kingsley Coman scores as United finish bottom and are out of the Champions League |date=13 December 2023 |access-date=29 May 2024 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> Fernandes' captaincy came under scrutiny, despite being the football player who played the most minutes in world football, with 72 games and 6,666 minutes dating from 15 September 2022 to 2023.<ref>{{cite web |date=4 October 2023 |title=Fernandes plays most minutes in world football |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67011822 |access-date=20 October 2023 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=31 October 2023 |title=Does Manchester United Have A Bruno Fernandes Problem? |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jamesnalton/2023/10/31/does-manchester-united-have-a-bruno-fernandes-problem/?sh=70c4d11523f9 |access-date=14 February 2024 |website=[[Forbes]] |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=30 October 2023 |title=Bruno Fernandes: Roy Keane says Man Utd boss Erik ten Hag should strip midfielder of captaincy|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12996078/bruno-fernandes-roy-keane-says-man-utd-boss-erik-ten-hag-should-strip-midfielder-of-captaincy|access-date=14 February 2024 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> In January 2024, during the winter [[transfer window]], Fernandes was the recipient of a contract offer worth €100&nbsp;million from [[Saudi Pro League]] side [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]]. If he had accepted the offer, he would have joined his national teammate [[Rúben Neves]], as well as former manager [[Jorge Jesus]], who was keen on signing him. However, the deal was eventually turned down by Fernandes, who felt he had unfinished business at United, stating that he was "happy [...] focused on Man United".<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 February 2024 |title=Al-Hilal plot summer move for Bruno Fernandes after Man Utd star rejected huge offer in January transfer window|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/al-hilal-plot-summer-move-bruno-fernandes-man-utd-rejected-huge-offer-january-window/blt7e08a62db36be83f#cs3d1f14a8711ec337|access-date=14 February 2024 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 February 2024 |title=Saudi Public Investment Fund 'targets Bruno Fernandes' and other Manchester United transfer rumours|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/manchester-united-bruno-fernandes-transfer-28056716|access-date=6 November 2023 |website=[[Manchester Evening News]] |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 7 April 2024, Fernandes scored his 50th Premier League goal from {{convert|50|yards}} in a 2–2 draw against United's [[Liverpool F.C.–Manchester United F.C. rivalry|arch rivals]] [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at Old Trafford.<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 April 2024 |title=How Manchester United held Liverpool to draw on goals by Kobbie Mainoo, Bruno Fernandes|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/manchester-united-liverpool-live-updates-premier-league-score-result/svlGoNslyXIA/|access-date=8 April 2024 |website=[[The Athletic]] |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=7 April 2024 |title=Bruno Fernandes scores insane goal for Man Utd from centre-circle as shocking error from Liverpool youngster Jarell Quansah gifts hosts an equaliser against run of play|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/video-bruno-fernandes-insane-goal-man-utd-centre-circle-error-liverpool-jarell-quansah/bltd4cdaba3c0c1dd98|access-date=8 April 2024 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> He was then named Manchester United Player of the Month for April after scoring seven goals in six appearances that month.<ref>{{cite news|last=Holt|first=Matthew|title=Fernandes crowned Player of the Month for April|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-wins-manchester-united-player-of-the-month-for-april-2024/|date=3 May 2024|access-date=29 May 2024|publisher=Manchester United F.C.}}</ref> On 23 May, Fernandes won the Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year, becoming a three-time recipient of the award.<ref name="MUNPOTY24">{{cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-wins-sir-matt-busby-player-of-the-year-2023-24|first=Adam|last=Marshall|title=Bruno crowned Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year|publisher=Manchester United F.C.|date=23 May 2024|access-date=23 May 2024}}</ref> In the [[2024 FA Cup final]] against local rivals Manchester City, Fernandes assisted [[Kobbie Mainoo]]'s goal in an eventual 2–1 win for United, winning his second trophy with the club and his first as club captain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c25533v2yzxo|title=Full-time: Man City 1–2 Man Utd|publisher=BBC|date=25 May 2024|access-date=25 May 2024}}</ref> After the match, pundit and former United midfielder [[Roy Keane]] praised Fernandes: "I've been critical of Bruno over the years, but I've been proven wrong, his leadership was outstanding. I've always mentioned how brilliant he is as a player."<ref>{{cite news|last=Marsh|first=Charlotte|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/13865/13142901/man-utd-win-the-fa-cup-erik-ten-hag-says-he-will-go-somewhere-else-and-win-trophies-if-club-doesn-t-want-him|title=Man Utd win the FA Cup: Erik ten Hag says he will go somewhere else and win trophies if club doesn't want him|date=26 May 2024|access-date=26 May 2024|website=Sky Sports}}</ref> In July, Fernandes was linked with a move to Saudi Arabia, with two clubs in the Saudi Pro League interested in him,<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 July 2024 |title=Football gossip: Bruno Fernandes and Kevin de Bruyne linked with Saudi Arabia moves |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c9x81y1r13yo |access-date=17 July 2024 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> but these rumours were dispelled in August when his contract with Manchester United was extended to 30 June 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fernandes signs new contract |url=https://manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-signs-new-man-utd-contract-until-2027 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240814202518/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/bruno-fernandes-signs-new-man-utd-contract-until-2027 |archive-date=14 August 2024 |access-date=14 August 2024 |publisher=Manchester United F.C.}}</ref>
[[File:Bruno Fernandes 00-07-14.16.png|thumb|Fernandes with [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2025]]
On 29 September, Fernandes was sent off for a high challenge on [[James Maddison]] in United's 3–0 loss to [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] at [[Old Trafford]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bruno Fernandes admits he 'let Man Utd down' with red card in Tottenham loss|date=29 September 2024 |url=https://www.90min.com/bruno-fernandes-let-man-utd-down-red-card-tottenham}}</ref> However, the red card was overturned by [[The Football Association]], following a successful claim of wrongful dismissal by the referee.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bruno Fernandes Update|url= https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/the-fa-overturn-bruno-fernandes-red-card-after-dismissal-against-tottenham-hotspur-september-2024}}</ref> On 3 October, he was sent off for the second time in five days when he received two yellow cards in a 3–3 draw with [[FC Porto|Porto]] in the UEFA Europa League.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/41592734/man-united-bruno-fernandes-red-card-2nd-straight-game|title=Man United's Bruno Fernandes gets red card for second straight game|date=1 October 2024|access-date=3 October 2024|publisher=ESPN}}</ref> This made him the first United player to be sent off in consecutive matches since [[Eric Cantona]] in March 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/apr/12/which-players-have-been-sent-off-in-their-first-game-after-suspension-knowledge|title=Which players have been sent off in their first game after suspension?|date=12 April 2023|access-date=4 October 2024|website=The Guardian}}</ref> He made his 250th appearance for the club on 11 November, scoring the opening goal and assisting [[Alejandro Garnacho]] in a 3–0 win against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/match-report-from-man-utd-v-leicester-city-10-november-2024|title=Match report: United 3 Leicester City 0|date=11 November 2024|access-date=13 November 2024}}</ref> In the 2–0 loss to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton]] on 26 December, Fernandes received his third red card this season, becoming the first United player to receive three red cards in a season since [[Nemanja Vidić]] in the 2008–09 season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gott |first=Tom |date=27 December 2024 |title=Bruno Fernandes matches unwanted red card record against Wolves to leave Ruben Amorim 'frustrated' |url=https://www.90min.com/bruno-fernandes-matches-unwanted-red-card-record-wolves-leave-ruben-amorim-frustrated}}</ref> On 13 March 2025, Fernandes scored a hat-trick against [[Real Sociedad]] in a 4–1 second leg of the round of 16 in the UEFA Europa League, with a final score line of 5–2 across the two-legged tie.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester United 4–1 Real Sociedad: Bruno Fernandes hat-trick puts Red Devils into Europa League last eight |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cvgeq2wqp70t |access-date=2025-03-14 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> His performances in March, with two goals and two assists, including a 'sensational' direct free-kick against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] earned Fernandes his fifth [[Premier League Player of the Month]] award.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fernandes matches Rooney with fifth EA SPORTS Player of the Month award |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4273684 |access-date=2025-04-29 |publisher=Premier League |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 20 June, it was announced that Fernandes was one of six nominees for the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-20 |title=PFA Players' Player of the Year: Bruno Fernandes and Mohamed Salah among nominees |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cx23n4z20j9o |access-date=2025-06-20 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 30 August 2025, Fernandes scored his first Premier League goal of the [[2025–26 Premier League|2025–26 season]], a 97th minute penalty to win the game 3–2 against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match report: Manchester United 3 - 2 Burnley|url=https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/content/match-report-manchester-united-3-2-burnley |date=30 August 2025|access-date=21 September 2025 |website=burnleyfootballclub.com |publisher=Burnley F.C.}}</ref> A month later, on 20 September, Fernandes made his 200th league appearance for United against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], in which he scored his 100th goal for the club across all competitions in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match report: Manchester United 2-1 Chelsea |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/match-report-manchester-united-2-1-chelsea-200925 |access-date=21 September 2025|date=20 September 2025|website=ChelseaFC.com |publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref> After scoring in a 2–0 home win against Tottenham Hotspur on 7 February 2026, Fernandes became the second fastest player to make 200 goal contributions in Manchester United's history, with 104 goals and 96 assists.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hancock |first=Tom |date=7 February 2026 |title=Carrick revival helps Fernandes beat Ronaldo in reaching landmark |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4582561/carrick-revival-helps-fernandes-beat-ronaldo-in-reaching-landmark |url-status=live |access-date=9 February 2026 |publisher=Premier League}}</ref> On 15 March, Fernandes set a new Manchester United record for most assists in a single Premier League season when he registered his 16th assist of the 2025–26 campaign in a 3–1 win over Aston Villa, surpassing the previous mark of 15 set by [[David Beckham]] in 1999–2000.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fernandes overtakes Beckham to set Man Utd assists record |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4615270/fernandes-overtakes-beckham-to-set-new-man-utd-assist-record |website=www.premierleague.com |access-date=16 March 2026 |date=15 March 2026}}</ref> On 8 May, Fernandes was named as the [[FWA Footballer of the Year]], owing to his eight goals and 19 assists in the Premier League thus far. He became the first Manchester United player to win the award since [[Wayne Rooney]] in 2010.<ref name="fwa 26">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cn8pvvp6n0qo|title=Man Utd's Fernandes wins Football Writers' men's award|work=BBC Sport|first=Simon|last=Stone|date=8 May 2026|access-date=8 May 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://footballwriters.co.uk/editorial/bruno-fernandes-is-footballer-of-the-year-and-bunny-shaw-is-womens-football-of-the-year/|title=Bruno Fernandes is Footballer of the Year and Bunny Shaw is Women's Football of the Year.|first=Gerry |last=Cox|publisher=Football Writers' Association|access-date=8 May 2026|date=8 May 2026}}</ref> On 17 May, Fernandes equalled the Premier League record for most assists in a single season, registering his 20th assist of the 2025–26 campaign in Manchester United's match against Nottingham Forest. The record was previously held jointly by [[Thierry Henry]] and [[Kevin De Bruyne]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 May 2026|title=Fernandes ties Premier League assist record alongside Henry and De Bruyne |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/bruno-fernandes-premier-league-assist-record-how-many-b2977823.html |access-date=17 May 2026|website=The Independent}}</ref> On 23 May, he was announced as the 2025–26 [[Premier League Player of the Season]].<ref name="pots26"/> He broke the Premier League single-season assist record on 24 May, after registering his 21st assist of the campaign in Manchester United's 3–0 away victory against Brighton & Hove Albion, setting up [[Patrick Dorgu]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-24 |title=Fernandes claims Premier League assist record outright ahead of Henry and De Bruyne |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/bruno-fernandes-premier-league-assist-record-how-many-b2982784.html |access-date=2026-05-24 |website=The Independent |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
===2012–2017: Youth level===
[[File:Bruno Miguel Borges Fernandes.jpg|thumb|right|Fernandes playing for [[Portugal Olympic football team|Portugal]] at the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2016 Summer Olympics]]]]
With the [[Portugal national under-20 football team|Portugal under-20s]], Fernandes participated in the [[2014 Toulon Tournament]]. In this competition, he played four out, scoring against [[Chile national under-20 football team|Chile]] in a group stage match, helping Portugal to a third-place finish.

Fernandes represented [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]], under-20, [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21]] and [[Portugal national under-23 football team|under-23 levels]], for a total of 28 [[Cap (sport)|caps]]. Prior to his international debut, he was named [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the under-21 team by coach [[Rui Jorge]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Steve |last=Sutcliffe |title=Manchester United: Can Bruno Fernandes translate his talent and confidence into success at Old Trafford? |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51285178 |website=BBC Sport |date=29 January 2020 |access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> He scored four goals and provided four assist in Portugal under-21s [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualification campaign]], helping them to qualify for the 2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/0257-0decf6068113-c9408f90eed8-1000--portugal-make-light-work-of-israel/ |title=Portugal make light work of Israel |publisher=UEFA |first=Carlos |last=Machado |date=10 October 2013 |access-date=11 October 2013}}</ref> In June, Fernandes took part in the 2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship, helping Portugal to a group stage finish, and scoring a goal against [[Serbia national under-21 football team|Serbia]] in the opening match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2021138--portugal-vs-serbia/?referrer=%2Funder21%2Fseason%3D2017%2Fmatches%2Fround%3D2000645%2Fmatch%3D2021138%2Findex |title=Portugal-Serbia &#124; Under-21|publisher=[[UEFA]]|access-date=11 November 2021}}</ref>

Fernandes represented [[Portugal Olympic football team|Portugal]] in the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/selecao/noticias/interior/os-18-convocados-de-rui-jorge-para-os-jogos-olimpicos-5284354.html |title=Os 17 convocados de Rui Jorge para os Jogos Olímpicos |trans-title=The 17 called up by Rui Jorge for the Olympic Games |newspaper=O Jogo |location=Porto |language=pt |date=14 July 2016 |access-date=12 September 2017 |archive-date=30 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130234318/https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/selecao/noticias/interior/os-18-convocados-de-rui-jorge-para-os-jogos-olimpicos-5284354.html |url-status=dead}}</ref> He started every game, as the team reached the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Notícias/Notícia/news/8190/contextid/174 |title=Vitória na estreia |trans-title=Win in debut |publisher=Portuguese Football Federation |language=pt |date=4 August 2016 |access-date=12 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Notícias/Notícia/news/8222/contextid/174 |title=Portugal vence e garante quartos de final|trans-title=Portugal win and confirm quarter-finals |publisher=Portuguese Football Federation |language=pt |date=7 August 2016 |access-date=12 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Notícias/Notícia/news/8235/contextid/174 |title=Portugal assegura primeiro lugar|trans-title=Portugal confirm first place |publisher=Portuguese Football Federation |language=pt |date=10 August 2016 |access-date=12 September 2017}}</ref>

===2017–2018: Senior and World Cup debuts===
[[File:Bruno Fernandes 2018 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Fernandes with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Overlooked for selection by Portugal during his spell in Italy, Fernandes was first chosen on 28 August 2017, replacing the injured [[Pizzi (Portuguese footballer)|Pizzi]] for [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifiers]] against the [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] and [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] to be played the next month, although he did not play in either match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rr.sapo.pt/noticia/92067/bruno_fernandes_chamado_para_o_lugar_de_pizzi |title=Bruno Fernandes chamado para o lugar de Pizzi|trans-title=Bruno Fernandes called in place of Pizzi |publisher=Rádio Renascença |language=pt |date=28 August 2017 |access-date=12 September 2017}}</ref> Fernandes won his first full cap on 10 November 2017, replacing [[Manuel Fernandes (footballer, born 1986)|Manuel Fernandes]] for the last 34 minutes of the 3–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] win over [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] in [[Viseu]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/amigaveis-selecoes/artigos/portugal-vence-arabia-saudita-com-golos-de-manuel-fernandes-goncalo-guedes-e-joao-mario |title=Portugal vence Arábia Saudita com golos de Manuel Fernandes, Gonçalo Guedes e João Mário |trans-title=Portugal beat Saudi Arabia with goals from Manuel Fernandes, Gonçalo Guedes and João Mário |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt |date=10 November 2017 |access-date=11 November 2017}}</ref>

He was then selected by [[Fernando Santos (Portuguese footballer)|Fernando Santos]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/portugal-world-cup-squad |title=Nearly half Portugal's Euro squad to miss World Cup |publisher=Special Broadcasting Service |date=17 May 2018 |access-date=18 May 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 7 June with a header in the last warm-up match before the tournament, a 3–0 defeat of [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] at the [[Estádio da Luz]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44373997 |title=Portugal 3–0 Algeria |website=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2018 |access-date=8 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao/portugal/bruno-fernandes-foi-o-meu-primeiro-golo-de-cabeca-como-profissional |title=Bruno Fernandes: "Foi o meu primeiro golo de cabeça como profissional"|trans-title=Bruno Fernandes: «It was my first goal with the head as a professional» |website=Maisfutebol |publisher=IOL |language=pt |date=7 June 2018 |access-date=8 June 2018}}</ref> Fernandes' first World Cup game took place on 15 June, when he played 66 minutes in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup Group B#Portugal vs Spain|3–3 group stage]] draw against [[Spain national football team|Spain]], being [[Penalty card#Yellow card|booked]] in the process.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/15/portugal-vs-spain-world-cup-2018-live-score-latest-updates/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/15/portugal-vs-spain-world-cup-2018-live-score-latest-updates/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Cristiano Ronaldo scores sensational hat-trick as Portugal hold Spain in instant World Cup classic |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |first1=Sam |last1=Wallace |first2=Rob |last2=Bagchi |date=15 June 2018 |access-date=15 June 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref> On 30 June, Portugal were eliminated following a 2–1 defeat to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in the last 16.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439361 |title=Uruguay 2–1 Portugal |website=BBC Sport |last=Rose |first=Gary |date=30 June 2018 |access-date=1 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701010039/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439361 |archive-date=1 July 2018}}</ref>

===2018–2021: Nations League title and subsequent struggles===
Fernandes was selected for three matches in the league phase of the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League]] group stage,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/teams/players/250059115--bernardo-silva/statistics/ |title=Bernardo Silva |publisher=UEFA |access-date=26 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2024021--poland-vs-portugal/ |title=Poland vs Portugal |publisher=UEFA |access-date=26 February 2019}}</ref> helping the hosts Portugal qualify to [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|the inaugural Nations League Finals]] in June 2019. In the UEFA Nations League Finals, Fernandes played both matches as Portugal defeated the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] 1–0 in Porto to win the trophy.<ref>{{cite news |first=Daniel |last=Taylor |author-link=Daniel Taylor (journalist) |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jun/09/portugal-netherlands-nations-league-final-match-report |title=Portugal win Nations League as Gonçalo Guedes does for the Netherlands |website=[[The Guardian]] |location=Estádio do Dragão |date=9 June 2019 |access-date=2 February 2020}}</ref> For his performances throughout the competition, he was named in the "Team of the Tournament".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/0253-0d821e23494c-f0c94c4974b3-1000--uefa-nations-league-finals-team-of-the-tournament/ |title=UEFA Nations League Finals: Team of the Tournament |publisher=UEFA |date=10 June 2019 |access-date=10 June 2019}}</ref>

Fernandes was named in Portugal's final squad for the delayed [[UEFA Euro 2020]] tournament, appearing in all games of the eventual round of 16 exit to [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pt.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/news/0269-1252942bc164-e2eac2467985-1000--convocados-de-portugal-para-o-euro-2020/|title=Convocados de Portugal para o EURO 2020|date=20 May 2021|publisher=[[UEFA]]|access-date=11 November 2021}}{{dead link|date=March 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Fernandes went on to be criticised for his performances during the tournament as he struggled to replicate his club form for Portugal. After being heavily fatigued and overshadowed by other teammates, he was dropped from the starting line-up for the final group stage match.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/bruno-fernandes-man-utd-portugal-24410128|title=Roy Keane gives verdict on Fernandes as Man Utd star dropped by Portugal again|first=Gareth|last=Bicknell|date=28 June 2021|newspaper=[[Daily Mirror]]|accessdate=11 November 2021}}</ref>

===2022–present: National team breakthrough===
On 29 March 2022, Fernandes scored both goals in Portugal's 2–0 win over [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]] in the final of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|World Cup qualification play-offs]] to ensure Portugal's qualification for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 tournament in Qatar]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/60907078 |title=Bruno Fernandes sends Portugal to World Cup|first=Emlyn|last=Begley|date=29 March 2022|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=31 March 2022}}</ref>

[[File:BFernandesWC22.jpg|thumb|upright|Fernandes after scoring in a group stage game against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]|253x253px]]
In October, he was named in Portugal's preliminary 55-man squad for the 2022 FIFA World Cup in Qatar,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/rumor-portugal-reportedly-announce-provisional-55-man-squad-2022-fifa-world-cup-liverpool-star-receives-surprise-call|title=Portugal reportedly name provisional 55-man squad for 2022 FIFA World Cup; Liverpool star receives surprise call up|publisher=Sportskeeda|first=Dakir Mohammed|last=Thanveer|date=25 October 2022|access-date=9 November 2022}}</ref> being included in the final 26-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|title=Os 26 convocados de Portugal: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio e Matheus Nunes chamados|trans-title=Portugal select 26: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio and Matheus Nunes called|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=10 November 2022|access-date=10 November 2022}}</ref> On 25 November, Fernandes provided two assists in Portugal's 3–2 group stage win against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Adriana |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/portugal-por/story/4805137/cristiano-ronaldo-becomes-first-man-to-score-in-5-world-cups |title=Portugal's Cristiano Ronaldo becomes first male player to score in 5 World Cups |date=24 November 2022 |access-date=24 November 2022 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> Three days later, Fernandes scored both of Portugal's goals in a 2–0 victory over Uruguay, securing his team's qualification to the knockout stages.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Whitehead |first=Jacob |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3946148/2022/11/28/portugal-uruguay-result/ |title=Portugal vs Uruguay result: Fernandes double secures progression for Portuguese |date=28 November 2022 |access-date=28 November 2022 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> On 6 December, he provided an assist for [[Pepe (footballer, born February 1983)|Pepe]], who scored Portugal's second goal in a thrashing 6–1 win in the round of 16 match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] and became the second-oldest player to ever score in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |last=Singh |first=Sanjesh |title=Pepe Becomes Second-Oldest Player to Score in a World Cup vs. Switzerland |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/pepe-becomes-second-oldest-player-185049562.html |website=NBC Sports |publisher=Yahoo! Sports |access-date=6 December 2022 |date=6 December 2022}}</ref> Portugal were eliminated in the quarter-finals after losing 1–0 to [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref>{{cite web |date=10 December 2022 |title=Morocco 1–0 Portugal: World Cup 2022 quarter-final – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/10/morocco-portugal-world-cup-2022-quarter-final-live |access-date=11 December 2022 |website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ronaldo equals men's international appearance record |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/ronaldo-equals-mens-international-appearance-record |publisher=FIFA |access-date=17 December 2022}}</ref> Despite Portugal's elimination, Fernandes finished the tournament as the joint-top assister with three assists.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/top-assisters-at-world-cup-qatar-2022 |title=Top assisters at Qatar 2022 |publisher=FIFA |access-date=26 December 2022}}</ref>

His World Cup form continued during the [[UEFA Euro 2024]] [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|qualifiers]] in March, providing two assists and a brace against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in a 3–0 win on 17 June.<ref>{{cite web |title=Euro 2024 Portugal cilindra Bósnia com 'show' de Bruno Fernandes |date=17 June 2023 |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/portugal-cilindra-bosnia-com-show-de-bruno-fernandes-veja-os-golos-2023081004033895407}}</ref> On 8 September, on his 29th birthday, Fernandes scored the only goal of an away win over [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Bruno Fernandes brilha e Portugal bate a Eslováquia fora de casa nas Eliminatórias da Euro |date=8 September 2023 |url=https://trivela.com.br/europa/portugal-eslovaquia-eliminatorias/}}</ref> On 11 September, he scored a goal and provided a hat-trick of assists in a 9–0 home defeat of [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]], the former's biggest win in international history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/portugal/selecao-nacional/portugal-9-0-luxemburgo-cronica|title=Portugal 9–0 Luxemburgo (crónica)|trans-title=Portugal 9–0 Luxembourg (report)|publisher=Mais Futebol|first=Pedro|last=Lemos|language=pt|date=11 September 2023|access-date=11 September 2023}}</ref> In the reverse fixture against Slovakia, on 13 November, Fernandes provided a brace of assists in a 3–2 win, leading Portugal to qualify for [[Euro 2024]], marking the nation's fastest qualification to a major tournament in their history.<ref>{{cite news |title=Portugal já está no Euro-2024 (e com a qualificação mais rápida de sempre!) |url=https://www.abola.pt/selecao/noticias/portugal-ja-esta-no-euro-2024-e-com-a-qualificacao-mais-rapida-de-sempre-2023101320423428087|access-date=13 October 2023 |agency=Abola}}</ref> Fernandes finished the qualifying campaign as the top assister with eight assists, with Portugal topping their qualifying group, and setting a new national team record of ten consecutive wins.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/0253-0d80578af302-67dcd0042fc2-1000--lukaku-sets-new-european-qualifiers-scoring-record/|title=Lukaku sets new European Qualifiers scoring record|date=19 November 2023|publisher=UEFA}}</ref>

On 21 May 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=21 May 2024 |title=Convocados para o Euro 2024 |trans-title=Called up for Euro 2024 |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45104 |language=pt |publisher=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |access-date=21 May 2024}}</ref> On 22 June, Fernandes scored Portugal's third goal in a 3–0 win against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]], securing his country's qualification to the [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout phase|knockout phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/cristiano-ronaldo-continues-to-break-records-n/ |title=Cristiano Ronaldo continues to break records |website=en.as.com |date=22 June 2024 |access-date=22 June 2024}}</ref> In Portugal's [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] match against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]], he played the full 120 minutes and scored the team's second kick of the [[penalty shootout]] which they won 3–0.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036201--portugal-vs-slovenia/lineups/ |title=Portugal vs Slovenia: Line-ups |access-date=3 July 2024 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref> Portugal were eliminated in the quarter-finals to [[France national football team|France]] after losing 5–3 in another penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt |title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens) |work=BBC Sport |first=Emma |last=Sanders |date=5 July 2024 |access-date=6 July 2024}}</ref>

On 16 November 2025, Fernandes scored a hat-trick in a 9–1 win over [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|FIFA World Cup qualification]], securing his nation's spot at the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 tournament in North America]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Rose |first=Gary |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c0mxyj1j9rjt |title=Portugal 9–1 Armenia |publisher=BBC Sport |date=16 November 2025}}</ref>

==Player profile==

===Style of play===
An [[attacking midfielder]], Fernandes is a direct, energetic [[box-to-box]] [[playmaker]] who is capable of both taking on defenders and setting the rhythm of play.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=Bruno Fernandes age, position, Man Utd shirt number, stats, style |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/facts-on-man-utd-new-signing-in-transfer-window-bruno-fernandes |access-date=10 July 2020 |publisher=Manchester United F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Cox |author-link=Michael Cox (journalist) |title=Bruno Fernandes: the man who is at his most dangerous when he stands still |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1669101/2020/03/14/bruno-fernandes-manchester-united-man-utd-tactics-goal-cox/ |url-access=subscription |date=13 March 2020 |work=The Athletic |access-date=29 July 2020}}</ref> Directness also means that Fernandes tends to take a lot of risks with the type and level of passes he attempts to complete. However, despite being prone to turnovers, he typically presses the opposition right after losing possession.<ref>{{cite web |first1=Laurie |last1=Whitwell |first2=Tom |last2=Worville |title=Bruno's passes are risky, but the rewards are well worth it |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1956276/2020/07/29/bruno-fernandes-manchester-united-passing-risk-reward/ |url-access=subscription |date=29 July 2020 |work=The Athletic |access-date=29 July 2020}}</ref> Fernandes boasts a prolific goalscoring record from the midfield position. He frequently shoots from outside the penalty area and is an accurate [[Free kick (association football)|free-kick]]<ref name=":0" /> and [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] taker.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/bruno-fernandes-penalty-secret-technique-man-utd-stars-spot-kick-/x98oqu53kt4j1r6lwbnr59get |title=Does Bruno Fernandes have a penalty secret? Technique behind Man Utd star's spot-kick success |website=Goal (website) |last=Kelly |first=Ryan |date=22 November 2020 |access-date=1 June 2021}}</ref> His movement off the ball is also key, with him often roaming around the attacking areas of the pitch, or dropping deep to pick up possession.<ref name=":0" /> As well as operating in the attacking midfielder role, he can also operate in a deeper [[central midfield]] role, or as a [[second striker]].<ref name=":0" /> During his time at Manchester United, under [[Erik ten Hag]], Fernandes also played on the [[Winger (association football)|right wing]] on many occasions, due to his [[Cross (association football)|crossing]] ability, which made him an effective [[Assist (association football)|assist]] provider.<ref>{{cite web |first=Carl |last=Anka |title=Why Bruno Fernandes frequently plays on the right wing for Manchester United |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4045574/2023/01/09/bruno-fernandes-right-wing/ |url-access=subscription |date=9 January 2023 |work=The Athletic |access-date=17 August 2024}}</ref>

===Reception and image===
Regarding his creativity and goalscoring ability, since joining the Premier League in 2020, Fernandes has created more chances than any other player in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |title=In numbers: Fernandes is having one of the most creative seasons in Premier League history |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4623310/has-fernandes-delivered-the-most-creative-season-in-history |website=Premier League |access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref> In the 2025–26 season, he set a new [[Premier League records and statistics#Assists|Premier League record for the most assists in a single campaign]] with 21, surpassing the previous record of 20 assists jointly held by [[Thierry Henry]] in 2002–03 and [[Kevin De Bruyne]] in 2019–20,<ref>{{cite news |title=Man Utd's Fernandes breaks Premier League assists record on final day of season |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/man-utds-fernandes-breaks-premier-league-assists-record-final-day-season-2026-05-24/ |work=Reuters |date=24 May 2026 |access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref> Manchester City manager [[Pep Guardiola]] once said, "Bruno's influence is outstanding. Unbelievable. Today saw a few games, the last games and I said: 'this guy's creativity is one of the best I've ever seen'."<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-manchester-united-fa-cup-final-pep-guardiola-preview-63852150|title=Guardiola: Players so focused|date=24 May 2024|access-date=16 August 2024|publisher=Manchester City}}</ref> In 2023, Manchester City and Belgian midfielder Kevin De Bruyne rated him as the best player in his position in Premier League commenting, "I think he's [Fernandes] a creative machine and just in general."<ref name=":1">{{cite news |url=https://sportsbrief.com/football/47577-kevin-de-bruyne-snubs-odegaard-picks-bruno-fernandes-midfielder-epl/|title=Kevin De Bruyne Picks Bruno Fernandes As Best Creative Midfielder Ahead of Odegaard|date=26 August 2023 |access-date=16 August 2024|publisher=Sports Brief}}</ref> former Manchester United defender [[Rio Ferdinand]] commented that Fernandes "is a player who knows how to create chances [...], who can for bit of imagination, creativity, the patience around the box, the ability to hit a ball from the edge of the box an put in the back of net, [...] manipulate and take ball".<ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pfsNilUXE_Q&ab_channel=RioFerdinandPresentsFIVE|title=Bruno Fernandes Finally Joins Manchester United|author=Rio Ferdinand present FIVE|via=YouTube|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> Ferdinand also praised his leadership abilities, stating "he was one of the players in the game that lead's by example".<ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uJrzK4bQFos&ab_channel=ManUtdForever|title=Rio Ferdinand praises Bruno Fernandes |author=Man Utd Forever|via=YouTube|access-date=11 September 2020}}</ref> Former Manchester United coach [[Ole Gunnar Solskjær]] stated that Fernandes was a "bit of a mix between [[Paul Scholes]] and [[Juan Sebastián Verón]]".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/11941700/bruno-fernandes-a-mix-of-paul-scholes-and-juan-sebastian-veron-says-ole-gunnar-solskjaer|title=Bruno Fernandes a mix of Paul Scholes and Juan Sebastián Verón, says Ole Gunnar Solskjaer|date=24 February 2020 |access-date=24 February 2020|publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> Fernandes goalscoring abilities have also drew comparisons with former Chelsea midfielder [[Frank Lampard]], after breaking his record of being the highest-scoring midfielder in Europe in a single season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.planetfootball.com/quick-reads/comparing-bruno-fernandes-2020-21-with-frank-lampard-and-steven-gerrards-best-seasons/|title=Comparing Bruno Fernandes' 2020–21 with Lampard & Gerrard's best seasons|date=22 May 2021 |access-date=22 May 2021|publisher=Planet Football}}</ref>

During his career, Fernandes has faced criticism for his on-field behaviour, particularly regarding his body language and emotional reactions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gary Neville criticizes Bruno Fernandes' behavior during matches|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12998765/gary-neville-criticizes-bruno-fernandes-behavior-during-matches|publisher=Sky Sports|access-date=26 February 2025|date=9 January 2023|language=en}}</ref> Pundits such as [[Gary Neville]] and [[Roy Keane]] have criticised his tendency to complain to referees, wave his arms in frustration, and visibly criticise teammates during matches. Neville has described his behaviour as "petulant" and suggested that such actions are unhelpful for a captain tasked with leading by example.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fernandes' captaincy at Man Utd questioned after frustrated display|url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/fernandes-captaincy-man-utd-questioned-after-frustrated-display-2023-03-07/|publisher=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2025|date=7 March 2023|language=en}}</ref> Similarly, Keane has questioned Fernandes' leadership qualities, criticizing him for "moaning and whinging" when the team was struggling, arguing that a captain should display resilience and composure.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bruno Fernandes: Roy Keane says Man Utd boss Erik ten Hag should strip midfielder of captaincy|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12996078/bruno-fernandes-roy-keane-says-man-utd-boss-erik-ten-hag-should-strip-midfielder-of-captaincy|publisher=Sky Sports|access-date=26 February 2025|date=6 November 2023|language=en}}</ref> Despite his significant contributions on the pitch, critics argue that his emotional outbursts and confrontational approach undermine his leadership and set a negative tone for the team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Emmanuel Petit slams Bruno Fernandes as 'diva' for his antics on the pitch|url=https://talksport.com/football/2050149/emmanuel-petit-bruno-fernandes-diva-man-utd/|publisher=TalkSport|access-date=26 February 2025|date=7 March 2023|language=en}}</ref>

===Goal celebration===
Fernandes has adopted a particular [[Goal celebration|goalscoring celebration]] throughout his career: after scoring a goal, he usually celebrates by covering his ears with both of his hands, as a tribute to his daughter, who covers her ears pretending not to hear him.<ref name=BrunoEarly/><ref name=Bruno99/>

==Sponsorship==
Fernandes is sponsored by sportswear company [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]. He wears Nike Mercurial Vapor [[Football boots|boots]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Bruno Fernandes 2021 – Net Worth, Salary and Endorsements |url=https://weallfollowunited.com/2021/08/26/bruno-fernandes-net-worth/|website=We All Follow United |date=26 August 2021}}</ref>

==Personal life==
When Fernandes moved to Italy at age 18 to join Novara, he was joined there by childhood sweetheart Ana Pinho; they married in 2015.<ref name=BrunoEarly/> The couple have a daughter (January 2017) and a son (September 2020).<ref name=BrunoEarly/> He has tattoos on both of his arms with the number 8, in which he tributes to his birth date and to his father, who was also a footballer and wore the number 8 shirt, during his playing career, the letter F symbolising his surname and the number 23 as a tribute to his debut with the Portugal national football team, when he was aged 23.<ref name=BrunoEarly/><ref name=Bruno99/>

Fernandes is multilingual; apart from his native Portuguese, he is fluent in Spanish, English, and Italian. He also speaks some French.<ref name=Bruno99/>

Fernandes also has a brother named Ricardo who plays in the ninth tier of English football for [[Roffey F.C.|Roffey]].<ref>{{cite news |title=It runs in the family! Bruno Fernandes' brother scores a screamer! |url=https://www.skysports.com/watch/video/sports/football/13118560/it-runs-in-the-family-bruno-fernandes-brother-scores-a-screamer |publisher=Sky Sports |date=19 April 2024}}</ref>

